    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Yes, at LEAST 3.&amp;nbsp; Kaladim for instance, you have citizen faction, merchant faction, warrior faction, paly faction, and bard faction.&amp;nbsp; Those are the ones I can think of off hand.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Freeport, of course there is Militia and Paly, but there are quest factions (like spirit faction for the shamans), good guilds, evil guilds, I believe citizens, Coalition of Tradesfolk and Tradesfolk Underground.&amp;nbsp; And of course, bard.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Neriak you have the queen and king factions, and merchants, and I'm not sure if the Cleric and Necro factions are related to king and queen or not, plus warrior faction that gets trashed from hunting in Crushbone.&amp;nbsp; My High Elf cleric can walk around freely in her natural state in the Foreign Quarter, has to avoid the warriors in the commons, and has to not only go in the 3rd quarter as DE but also has to colloborate with some, but not all, of the merchants in the necro guild.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The problem is that what quests and items may be important to you are not important to someone else and vice versa.&amp;nbsp; An Iksar, for example, could probably care less about the factions raised turning in bone chips.&amp;nbsp; My enchanter cares greatly.&amp;nbsp; I still don't dare to sit if Commander Quarg is around, even in Iksar form, unless I cast colloborate on him.&amp;nbsp; The merchants and other guards though in the Field of Bone, I can go as a high elf and they think I'm fine.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Likewise, you wouldn't a quest given by barbs in Halas for barbs would make you KOS or even unfriendly with the rogues of Halas, which is an&amp;nbsp;issue if you wish to bank.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
